1
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:43,360
The real reason Dad died was you!

2
00:02:43,440 --> 00:02:44,360
Remember that!

3
00:02:44,440 --> 00:02:47,840
No light from Dad. No starlight from Mom.

4
00:02:49,240 --> 00:02:50,800
I have no one.

5
00:02:50,880 --> 00:02:54,040
He's just a friend not caring,
not paying attention…

6
00:02:54,120 --> 00:02:56,240
So why am I this emotional?

7
00:02:56,320 --> 00:02:58,240
Because it has gone past just friends.

8
00:02:58,960 --> 00:03:00,560
Dad left all his shares to me?

9
00:03:01,160 --> 00:03:04,440
Yes. All the Be Rich shares
under Mr. Tritot's name

10
00:03:04,520 --> 00:03:06,520
were intended
to be given to you, Mr. Trai,

11
00:03:07,120 --> 00:03:08,440
along with this house as well.

12
00:03:08,520 --> 00:03:11,120
You got everything without having
to struggle for a damn thing.

13
00:03:11,200 --> 00:03:12,760
And in the end, what happened?

14
00:03:12,840 --> 00:03:13,960
Dad still didn't choose me.

15
00:03:14,480 --> 00:03:16,800
I really want to know,
when Dad was sitting in this chair,

16
00:03:16,880 --> 00:03:18,520
who did he piss off so badly?

17
00:03:18,600 --> 00:03:21,400
I'll talk about appointing
Be Rich's new chairman.

18
00:03:21,480 --> 00:03:23,160
Trai shouldn't get anything
from Dad anymore…

19
00:03:23,240 --> 00:03:24,400
especially that chair.

20
00:03:24,480 --> 00:03:26,880
I, Trai Bowornmongkolphong,

21
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:28,280
would like to nominate myself

22
00:03:28,360 --> 00:03:30,920
for the position of CEO of Be Rich.

23
00:03:34,480 --> 00:03:37,840
Hi. I'll take kale, lime,
chili, kaffir lime,

24
00:03:38,440 --> 00:03:40,480
and tomatoes.

25
00:03:40,560 --> 00:03:42,640
Big red ones, please.

26
00:03:42,720 --> 00:03:44,320
-Sure.
-Thanks.

27
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:50,720
TRANSACTION COMPLETE: 20,000 BAHT
FROM MR. RACHEN BOWORNMONGKOLPHONG

28
00:03:51,480 --> 00:03:54,000
Should I transfer the money
back to Mr. Rachen?

29
00:03:55,360 --> 00:03:56,200
No need.

30
00:03:57,720 --> 00:04:00,600
Hey! How did you even find me?

31
00:04:00,680 --> 00:04:02,920
Did you put a tracking device on my phone?

32
00:04:04,040 --> 00:04:06,000
I just followed your motorbike.

33
00:04:06,840 --> 00:04:08,480
I wasn't lying to you.

34
00:04:08,560 --> 00:04:10,520
I really am buying groceries
for a customer.

35
00:04:11,120 --> 00:04:12,120
Look.

36
00:04:15,920 --> 00:04:17,040
I didn't say anything.

37
00:04:18,160 --> 00:04:21,080
I just want to make
the 20,000 I paid worth it.

38
00:04:28,200 --> 00:04:29,200
Here.

39
00:04:32,920 --> 00:04:34,960
Do you have something you want from me?

40
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:39,560
You already know that Trai wants
to be the CEO of Be Rich, right?

41
00:04:40,400 --> 00:04:42,680
Yes. I saw it in the news.

42
00:04:42,760 --> 00:04:44,120
So who are you rooting for?

43
00:04:45,560 --> 00:04:46,600
Do I have to root for someone?

44
00:04:47,240 --> 00:04:49,200
Yes. You should root for me.

45
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:55,520
Do you have feelings for me, Mr. Rachen?

46
00:04:58,480 --> 00:04:59,840
In the middle of the market?

47
00:04:59,920 --> 00:05:01,520
You ask so directly,

48
00:05:02,120 --> 00:05:03,440
without fearing the answer.

49
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:05,920
So you don't feel anything for me.

50
00:05:06,520 --> 00:05:07,720
Don't fall for me.

51
00:05:08,560 --> 00:05:10,800
Don't feel anything deep for me ever.

52
00:05:12,760 --> 00:05:14,080
Because you like Trai.

53
00:05:18,160 --> 00:05:19,440
I like myself.

54
00:05:20,080 --> 00:05:23,840
Especially when I have money.
That's when I like myself the most.

55
00:05:24,600 --> 00:05:26,280
I already told you

56
00:05:26,360 --> 00:05:29,240
I don't want to use my heart on anyone.

57
00:05:30,040 --> 00:05:31,800
If you give me your heart,

58
00:05:31,880 --> 00:05:33,320
it won't be worth anything.

59
00:05:34,040 --> 00:05:36,680
So don't.

60
00:05:36,760 --> 00:05:37,800
Please don't.

61
00:05:38,880 --> 00:05:40,440
I don't want you to get hurt.

62
00:05:45,960 --> 00:05:47,800
Then how much money do you want to have?

63
00:05:49,400 --> 00:05:52,160
How much? Well…

64
00:05:52,240 --> 00:05:55,120
enough to feel secure.

65
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:58,160
Enough to buy things
without checking the price.

66
00:06:07,840 --> 00:06:10,720
Around here? Which house is it?

67
00:06:12,240 --> 00:06:13,120
You're late.

68
00:06:15,440 --> 00:06:16,600
Mr. Trai?

69
00:06:17,760 --> 00:06:19,640
Were you stalking me?

70
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:23,600
I put a GPS tracker on your bike.

71
00:06:26,440 --> 00:06:27,640
Just kidding.

72
00:06:28,320 --> 00:06:30,480
Rachen followed you,
and I just did the same.

73
00:06:31,920 --> 00:06:35,000
I don't have time to play. I'm working.

74
00:06:37,160 --> 00:06:38,120
Working?

75
00:06:39,360 --> 00:06:40,480
This is your work.

76
00:06:46,360 --> 00:06:47,360
Mr. Tong?

77
00:06:48,160 --> 00:06:49,200
Yes, I'm Mr. Tong.

78
00:06:50,440 --> 00:06:51,560
Handsome, right?

79
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:55,400
Fake name but real number.
Did you even check?

80
00:06:56,680 --> 00:06:58,480
If I checked, would I even be here?

81
00:07:03,480 --> 00:07:04,480
So what do you want delivered?

82
00:07:06,480 --> 00:07:08,960
-Hurry.
-Me.

83
00:07:14,520 --> 00:07:16,280
Oh? Hey.

84
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:24,440
So how did you know I'd accept your order?

85
00:07:26,520 --> 00:07:27,600
Did you hack the system?

86
00:07:28,200 --> 00:07:29,880
Don't overcomplicate it.

87
00:07:30,480 --> 00:07:33,160
You love money. You'd accept it anyway.

88
00:07:36,200 --> 00:07:37,440
Let's go.

89
00:07:38,440 --> 00:07:39,520
Look at the map to see where you go.

90
00:07:42,280 --> 00:07:43,240
What?

91
00:07:44,080 --> 00:07:45,440
This place?

92
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:48,360
Are you going to cancel it?

93
00:07:49,360 --> 00:07:51,360
If you do,
(Watch on www,kisskh,la to support Admin)

94
00:07:52,600 --> 00:07:55,240
I'll file a complaint. I'll report you.

95
00:07:55,320 --> 00:07:57,000
I'll send it to HQ,

96
00:07:57,080 --> 00:07:59,560
making it that you can't work
as a driver again.

97
00:08:03,160 --> 00:08:05,320
If you don't want a bad record, just go.

98
00:08:06,080 --> 00:08:06,920
Go, driver.

99
00:08:11,560 --> 00:08:13,440
Yes, sir, customer.

100
00:08:14,200 --> 00:08:15,360
Hey.

101
00:08:15,440 --> 00:08:17,960
Bye-bye, customer.

102
00:08:25,800 --> 00:08:26,880
You're still here?

103
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:29,920
The homeowner allowed me to stay.

104
00:08:31,080 --> 00:08:34,240
And you?
Did you ask Mr. Trai for permission?

105
00:08:35,640 --> 00:08:38,200
Ah, Mr. Rachen just stopped by
to pick something up.

106
00:08:48,360 --> 00:08:49,360
Hey.

107
00:08:49,440 --> 00:08:51,800
Mr. Rachen, have some manners, will you?

108
00:08:54,040 --> 00:08:55,960
Past Be Rich meeting documents?

109
00:08:57,240 --> 00:08:59,480
You really think you can work at Be Rich?

110
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:05,040
Do you even know
what income recognition suspension is?

111
00:09:06,160 --> 00:09:08,960
Fixed interest rates?

112
00:09:09,560 --> 00:09:13,360
Floating interest rates? MLR? MRR?

113
00:09:16,880 --> 00:09:18,000
You have no clue, do you?

114
00:09:19,400 --> 00:09:21,760
People aren't born knowledgeable.

115
00:09:21,840 --> 00:09:23,240
I can learn.

116
00:09:24,720 --> 00:09:26,160
Be Rich isn't a school.

117
00:09:26,760 --> 00:09:30,520
We need people who already know,
not people who come to learn.

118
00:09:31,120 --> 00:09:32,800
If you can't make Be Rich grow,

119
00:09:34,040 --> 00:09:36,160
don't become dead weight.

120
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:18,480
That's Trai's study.

121
00:10:23,400 --> 00:10:25,120
Outsiders aren't allowed inside.

122
00:10:26,920 --> 00:10:28,200
That's Dad's study.

123
00:10:28,280 --> 00:10:29,840
But now it belongs to Trai.

124
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:33,680
You should have been loyal to Dad
as much as you are to Trai.

125
00:10:34,600 --> 00:10:36,800
Trai never ordered me.
I'm doing this willingly.

126
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:41,480
Dad's body hasn't even been cremated yet,
and you found a new branch to cling to.

127
00:10:43,120 --> 00:10:45,720
It makes me wonder…

128
00:10:47,520 --> 00:10:49,920
did you approach Trai just to survive?

129
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:51,360
Or…

130
00:10:52,560 --> 00:10:54,760
did you plan everything from the start?

131
00:10:58,520 --> 00:11:00,280
Does Trai trust you because he's stupid,

132
00:11:01,240 --> 00:11:02,840
or are you two working together?

133
00:11:07,680 --> 00:11:08,840
Did you…

134
00:11:11,160 --> 00:11:13,440
have a hand in Dad's death?

135
00:11:15,920 --> 00:11:17,600
You were once a suspect yourself.

136
00:11:17,680 --> 00:11:19,480
Don't you know what it feels like?

137
00:11:23,760 --> 00:11:26,360
I didn't kill Mr. Tritot.

138
00:11:30,120 --> 00:11:32,760
But I was so damn happy

139
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:35,440
that he finally died.

140
00:11:37,120 --> 00:11:38,600
-Mr. Rachen.
-Let go!

141
00:11:38,680 --> 00:11:40,840
Mr. Rachen, please calm down.

142
00:11:44,720 --> 00:11:46,520
Mr. Tritot is already dead.

143
00:11:47,440 --> 00:11:48,880
The living have to move on.

144
00:11:49,480 --> 00:11:50,800
But if you can't move on,

145
00:11:51,480 --> 00:11:53,040
why don't you follow him and die?

146
00:11:53,120 --> 00:11:54,920
-Hell must be pretty warm.
-Mr. Rachen.

147
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:56,000
Mr. Rachen. Mr. Rachen.

148
00:11:56,080 --> 00:11:57,520
Darin!

149
00:11:57,600 --> 00:11:58,680
Please calm down.

150
00:11:59,400 --> 00:12:00,840
-Please calm down.
-Damn it!

151
00:12:20,720 --> 00:12:23,880
Whoa, stop, stop.
We're about to fall into the sea.

152
00:12:24,880 --> 00:12:26,440
We're here!

153
00:12:39,120 --> 00:12:41,960
The total is 1,335 baht.

154
00:12:42,040 --> 00:12:44,320
Will you pay by QR or cash?

155
00:12:49,800 --> 00:12:52,480
-What's wrong?
-Feels like heatstroke.

156
00:12:54,480 --> 00:12:55,720
Huh?

157
00:12:57,800 --> 00:13:00,200
I think I'm about to pass out.

158
00:13:00,800 --> 00:13:01,920
Can you support me?

159
00:13:02,960 --> 00:13:05,760
If you can predict
the future that well, look.

160
00:13:06,880 --> 00:13:07,840
Beach chairs.

161
00:13:07,920 --> 00:13:09,360
Go sit down

162
00:13:09,440 --> 00:13:12,000
and order something cold to drink.

163
00:13:15,640 --> 00:13:17,880
-Then come with me.
-No.

164
00:13:20,440 --> 00:13:21,280
My key.

165
00:13:23,400 --> 00:13:24,920
If not, then don't go back.

166
00:13:27,600 --> 00:13:28,600
Ugh, I'm gonna faint.

167
00:13:28,680 --> 00:13:29,800
-I'm gonna faint.
-Hey.

168
00:13:29,880 --> 00:13:31,600
Hey. Give my key back right now.

169
00:13:32,360 --> 00:13:34,480
Hey! Mr. Trai.

170
00:13:35,880 --> 00:13:37,320
Mr. Trai.

171
00:13:38,560 --> 00:13:40,520
I'm gonna livestream this and expose you.

172
00:13:43,040 --> 00:13:45,240
I really can't handle it, you know?

173
00:13:46,320 --> 00:13:47,760
Do you have an inhaler?

174
00:13:51,160 --> 00:13:52,040
I don't.

175
00:13:55,240 --> 00:13:56,440
Or maybe I'm just hungry.

176
00:13:57,560 --> 00:13:58,600
How about this?

177
00:13:59,880 --> 00:14:02,480
Let's eat first, then you take me home,

178
00:14:02,560 --> 00:14:03,400
and I'll pay you everything then.

179
00:14:10,880 --> 00:14:12,920
I can trust you, right?

180
00:14:14,040 --> 00:14:17,200
You made me ride
all the way here just to eat?

181
00:14:19,760 --> 00:14:21,000
Come on.

182
00:14:21,880 --> 00:14:24,320
I have to go back
to the company soon anyway.

183
00:14:24,400 --> 00:14:28,200
I have to go back into… Just
thinking about it is already suffocating.

184
00:14:28,280 --> 00:14:30,720
Can't I just breathe freely for a bit

185
00:14:30,800 --> 00:14:32,480
and clear my head first?

186
00:14:55,320 --> 00:14:56,320
Is that gonna take you all day?

187
00:14:57,520 --> 00:14:59,560
-Here, I'll crack it for you.
-Hey, no need.

188
00:14:59,640 --> 00:15:00,640
I'll do it myself.

189
00:15:11,080 --> 00:15:12,360
Got it.

190
00:15:18,400 --> 00:15:19,480
Good job.

191
00:15:22,160 --> 00:15:23,600
Here. For you.

192
00:15:24,240 --> 00:15:25,320
Why don't you eat it yourself?

193
00:15:25,400 --> 00:15:28,320
Haven't you heard?
Deshelling shrimp or crab for someone

194
00:15:29,240 --> 00:15:31,120
is one way of showing love.

195
00:15:33,280 --> 00:15:35,160
And haven't you heard

196
00:15:35,240 --> 00:15:38,400
you can just order
pre-cracked crab like this?

197
00:15:39,480 --> 00:15:42,120
Crab meat in containers.

198
00:15:42,200 --> 00:15:44,840
Easy, convenient, no deshelling needed.

199
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:54,360
You're really scared.

200
00:15:56,640 --> 00:15:57,800
Scared of what?

201
00:15:58,360 --> 00:16:00,120
You went to see me
at Be Rich yesterday, right?

202
00:16:05,120 --> 00:16:07,720
I just passed by.
Then I went straight back to work.

203
00:16:09,840 --> 00:16:11,120
You saw me but didn't say hi.

204
00:16:11,880 --> 00:16:13,800
I called you, but you didn't answer.

205
00:16:15,320 --> 00:16:16,920
But Kanah told me everything.

206
00:16:17,720 --> 00:16:20,360
You avoided me
because you're afraid of your own heart.

207
00:16:22,760 --> 00:16:23,840
Afraid of what?

208
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:26,560
Afraid of falling in love with me, right?

209
00:16:37,440 --> 00:16:38,560
I…

210
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:40,680
I…

211
00:16:41,880 --> 00:16:43,320
I should go.

212
00:16:55,640 --> 00:16:58,520
Kanah, seriously,
why did you tell him everything?!

213
00:17:07,760 --> 00:17:08,760
Hey.

214
00:17:09,600 --> 00:17:11,160
Why is my heart beating so hard?

215
00:17:12,280 --> 00:17:14,440
This fast and it'll jump out.

216
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:17,920
Don't fall for it. Don't get shaken.

217
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:19,280
Don't cause trouble for yourself.

218
00:17:19,880 --> 00:17:21,360
You can't love yet, Pakbung.

219
00:17:21,440 --> 00:17:23,280
You can't love. Got it?

220
00:17:23,360 --> 00:17:25,720
No love. It's a no-no.

221
00:17:25,800 --> 00:17:28,000
Absolutely no love, Pakbung.

222
00:17:29,560 --> 00:17:32,320
You can't, Pakbung.

223
00:17:35,280 --> 00:17:36,360
When you're already in love,

224
00:17:38,200 --> 00:17:40,000
you can't escape it,
no matter how hard you try.

225
00:17:43,040 --> 00:17:44,280
I don't…

226
00:18:08,600 --> 00:18:09,920
Come on, let's get out of the rain.

227
00:18:18,680 --> 00:18:19,680
WALK AND EAT FOOD FESTIVAL

228
00:18:20,680 --> 00:18:21,920
Whoa.

229
00:18:24,160 --> 00:18:25,040
-Hey.
-Huh?

230
00:18:25,680 --> 00:18:26,520
My key.

231
00:18:26,600 --> 00:18:28,960
Let's find shelter first.
Riding back now would be dangerous.

232
00:18:29,040 --> 00:18:30,200
Come on. Over there.

233
00:18:32,600 --> 00:18:34,560
-Where are they going?
-No idea. Hey.

234
00:18:35,280 --> 00:18:36,320
Stay put for now.

235
00:18:41,080 --> 00:18:42,040
You okay?

236
00:18:47,640 --> 00:18:48,960
Do you have any rooms available?

237
00:18:49,040 --> 00:18:50,280
Yes. How many rooms?

238
00:18:50,360 --> 00:18:52,400
I'm not staying overnight.

239
00:18:53,040 --> 00:18:55,320
How are you going to get back?
It's raining really hard.

240
00:18:59,360 --> 00:19:00,440
So how many rooms?

241
00:19:01,880 --> 00:19:02,960
Two rooms.

242
00:19:03,040 --> 00:19:04,560
Two rooms, 5,000.

243
00:19:04,640 --> 00:19:07,080
Breakfast is 300. Total is 5,300.

244
00:19:07,680 --> 00:19:09,360
5,300?

245
00:19:11,200 --> 00:19:12,680
At least pull a knife out
if you're gonna rob us.

246
00:19:12,760 --> 00:19:14,000
So you won't take it.

247
00:19:14,960 --> 00:19:16,080
We'll take it.

248
00:19:17,760 --> 00:19:19,400
It's better than getting soaked.

249
00:19:26,800 --> 00:19:27,720
I spent all my cash on the food.

250
00:19:29,840 --> 00:19:30,680
You can transfer.

251
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:40,880
Battery's dead!

252
00:19:42,840 --> 00:19:45,200
We don't have
rental chargers for that model.

253
00:19:51,680 --> 00:19:54,240
Then I'll just sit…

254
00:19:56,200 --> 00:19:57,120
So delicate.

255
00:19:57,720 --> 00:19:59,840
Just a bit of rain
and you're already sick?

256
00:20:00,440 --> 00:20:02,600
This price includes
clothes to change into.

257
00:20:02,680 --> 00:20:04,040
So what'll it be?

258
00:20:04,120 --> 00:20:06,440
Stay, or get pneumonia?

259
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:26,600
If you're uncomfortable,

260
00:20:26,680 --> 00:20:28,760
once the rain stops, we can go home.

261
00:20:30,040 --> 00:20:31,080
How can we go back?

262
00:20:31,920 --> 00:20:34,520
I already paid over 2,000.

263
00:20:34,600 --> 00:20:35,640
What a waste.

264
00:20:39,600 --> 00:20:41,040
Then will you sleep with me?

265
00:20:44,360 --> 00:20:45,840
Will you sleep with me?

266
00:20:47,880 --> 00:20:51,120
Pakbung, you shouldn't ask a man that.

267
00:20:53,280 --> 00:20:55,200
If I don't ask,
how are we gonna make a deal?

268
00:20:55,800 --> 00:20:58,680
I paid for the room,

269
00:20:58,760 --> 00:20:59,760
so I'm the owner.

270
00:20:59,840 --> 00:21:01,680
If you want to sleep here,

271
00:21:01,760 --> 00:21:03,120
you have to pay first.

272
00:21:04,920 --> 00:21:07,600
-I thought…
-Thought what?

273
00:21:10,400 --> 00:21:14,000
Oh, that?

274
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:19,440
That's fine. Room split in half,

275
00:21:19,520 --> 00:21:22,120
handshake deal, 5,000. More than that?

276
00:21:22,200 --> 00:21:25,360
10,000 per hug. If clothes come off,

277
00:21:26,040 --> 00:21:27,440
100,000 per piece.

278
00:21:33,040 --> 00:21:34,000
You don't like it?

279
00:21:34,080 --> 00:21:35,920
I'm that kind of woman.

280
00:21:36,480 --> 00:21:39,760
No feelings, no pain. No money, no deal.

281
00:21:43,840 --> 00:21:46,760
Then… what if I pay for it all?

282
00:21:52,800 --> 00:21:54,680
You haven't told me how much your kiss is.

283
00:21:57,680 --> 00:21:58,640
Mr. Trai.

284
00:22:00,360 --> 00:22:01,800
You can't afford it.

285
00:22:02,960 --> 00:22:05,920
Pakbung, you should know my family's rich.

286
00:22:06,720 --> 00:22:08,560
Very rich.

287
00:22:10,480 --> 00:22:14,040
But normally,
you don't buy things like this.

288
00:22:14,120 --> 00:22:15,320
This isn't normal.

289
00:22:17,160 --> 00:22:19,080
It's only for someone special like you.

290
00:22:29,400 --> 00:22:31,720
Ugh, gross. You stink.

291
00:22:31,800 --> 00:22:34,080
You didn't shower this morning, did you?

292
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:38,160
Go to the bathroom. Go shower right now.

293
00:22:38,240 --> 00:22:40,480
So smelly. Go. Get in there.

294
00:22:42,320 --> 00:22:43,720
Don't come out.

295
00:22:43,800 --> 00:22:45,080
Take a shower.

296
00:22:45,160 --> 00:22:46,680
Hey, Pakbung.

297
00:22:50,320 --> 00:22:51,280
Run, Pakbung.

298
00:22:52,120 --> 00:22:53,960
If you stay, you're done for.

299
00:22:55,320 --> 00:22:56,560
Go.

300
00:22:57,120 --> 00:22:59,520
Why aren't you leaving?
You want to stay with Mr. Trai?

301
00:23:00,120 --> 00:23:01,560
Yes, I really do. Hey!

302
00:23:01,640 --> 00:23:03,320
No.

303
00:23:03,400 --> 00:23:04,800
Stop it.

304
00:23:04,880 --> 00:23:06,960
Get a grip. Get a grip.

305
00:23:15,960 --> 00:23:17,560
-Mr. Trai.
-That's Mr. Trai's voice.

306
00:23:19,120 --> 00:23:20,400
How did you even hear that?

307
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:23,000
What's wrong?

308
00:23:23,880 --> 00:23:26,160
Don't come closer. Don't come closer.

309
00:23:26,880 --> 00:23:29,880
Don't come closer. Don't.

310
00:23:29,960 --> 00:23:31,000
Hey.

311
00:23:31,080 --> 00:23:32,960
Don't come in, Pakbung. Don't come in.

312
00:23:33,040 --> 00:23:33,920
Mr. Trai,

313
00:23:34,000 --> 00:23:36,000
I'll help you! Hey!

314
00:24:04,040 --> 00:24:04,920
Hey!

315
00:24:08,080 --> 00:24:11,240
Hey. I told you not to come in.

316
00:24:12,560 --> 00:24:14,360
What do we do?

317
00:24:16,040 --> 00:24:16,960
We have to chase it off.

318
00:24:21,280 --> 00:24:22,400
-Hey!
-Stop, stop!

319
00:24:22,480 --> 00:24:24,360
That's an instant vasectomy. Stop.

320
00:24:25,320 --> 00:24:27,200
Then, go outside.

321
00:24:27,280 --> 00:24:29,160
Go. Go shake it off.

322
00:24:29,240 --> 00:24:34,480
I… I can't move.

323
00:24:34,560 --> 00:24:36,600
Then what do we do?

324
00:24:36,680 --> 00:24:39,160
What if it crawls up?

325
00:24:39,240 --> 00:24:40,200
I don't know.

326
00:24:41,240 --> 00:24:42,480
-Wrap… Wrap it.
-Wrap?

327
00:24:42,560 --> 00:24:44,640
Wrap what? Wrap what?

328
00:24:44,720 --> 00:24:46,000
Take it off. Wrap it.

329
00:24:46,080 --> 00:24:48,080
-Wrap it.
-How?

330
00:24:48,840 --> 00:24:50,440
-Wrap what? Wrap?
-Wrap!

331
00:24:50,520 --> 00:24:52,520
-Wrap?
-Hurry! Wrap it!

332
00:24:52,600 --> 00:24:54,520
-Hey!
-Do it.

333
00:24:59,200 --> 00:25:01,560
-Take it. Take it.
-Hey!

334
00:25:03,200 --> 00:25:04,360
Take it.

335
00:25:11,360 --> 00:25:12,520
What the hell is this?

336
00:25:22,040 --> 00:25:24,200
-Gec…
-Gec?

337
00:25:24,280 --> 00:25:25,240
Gec…

338
00:25:25,320 --> 00:25:26,560
Gec what?

339
00:25:26,640 --> 00:25:27,640
Gec…

340
00:25:28,160 --> 00:25:29,200
Gec…

341
00:25:30,240 --> 00:25:33,880
Gec… Gecko!

342
00:25:48,160 --> 00:25:49,240
It's gone, right?

343
00:25:54,440 --> 00:25:58,000
That's scarier than the gecko!

344
00:26:22,640 --> 00:26:24,160
Dad left Be Rich to me,

345
00:26:25,840 --> 00:26:27,480
so I want to do something for him
for once.

346
00:26:30,440 --> 00:26:33,240
But I let Darin work with me.
It's not because I pity her.

347
00:26:33,920 --> 00:26:36,200
I just want to give her what she deserves,

348
00:26:36,960 --> 00:26:40,320
something she never got
after she came into my family.

349
00:26:41,760 --> 00:26:42,800
Which is?

350
00:26:44,320 --> 00:26:45,640
Human dignity.

351
00:26:50,440 --> 00:26:51,760
So we're clear?

352
00:26:54,280 --> 00:26:57,280
Well, I don't have an issue with it.

353
00:27:00,920 --> 00:27:02,000
Then, your turn.

354
00:27:04,520 --> 00:27:05,640
My turn?

355
00:27:07,560 --> 00:27:09,120
I don't know what that is.

356
00:27:11,960 --> 00:27:13,240
Mr. Trai!

357
00:27:13,960 --> 00:27:14,960
Hey, why did you…

358
00:27:18,000 --> 00:27:21,120
I'm not letting you go
until you say how you feel.

359
00:27:23,960 --> 00:27:25,040
I've had my heart broken once.

360
00:27:26,240 --> 00:27:27,320
By whom? Huh?

361
00:27:28,920 --> 00:27:30,120
By my dad.

362
00:27:35,600 --> 00:27:36,680
I loved him.

363
00:27:37,960 --> 00:27:39,520
And I thought he loved me.

364
00:27:42,240 --> 00:27:43,240
I…

365
00:27:44,320 --> 00:27:46,840
I believed that was true love, pure love,

366
00:27:48,120 --> 00:27:49,880
a love where you stay,
care for each other,

367
00:27:50,560 --> 00:27:52,200
understand each other,

368
00:27:53,720 --> 00:27:55,200
support each other forever.

369
00:27:58,080 --> 00:28:01,080
But in the end, I got left behind.

370
00:28:19,520 --> 00:28:20,760
Mr. Trai…

371
00:28:22,400 --> 00:28:24,640
I think we should stay friends.

372
00:28:25,720 --> 00:28:28,560
Being friends is safer.

373
00:28:29,440 --> 00:28:31,760
Let's not try to cross the line.

374
00:28:58,320 --> 00:29:00,160
You really think we can be just friends?

375
00:29:04,080 --> 00:29:05,280
Sure.

376
00:29:07,480 --> 00:29:08,560
I guess.

377
00:29:14,800 --> 00:29:15,840
Maybe.

378
00:29:41,680 --> 00:29:43,200
We probably can't be friends anymore.

379
00:30:49,200 --> 00:30:50,480
Can you be quieter?

380
00:30:50,560 --> 00:30:51,640
-Excuse me.
-Sorry, sir.

381
00:30:53,280 --> 00:30:54,560
Pakbung already left?

382
00:30:55,600 --> 00:30:56,760
I don't see her bike anymore.

383
00:30:57,440 --> 00:30:58,320
Forget that for now.

384
00:30:58,400 --> 00:30:59,880
You have to rush back to the office now.

385
00:31:19,280 --> 00:31:21,480
Mr. Trai, wake up.

386
00:31:23,880 --> 00:31:25,800
-I bought soy milk…
-Oh.

387
00:31:25,880 --> 00:31:27,600
-…for you.
-Miss.

388
00:31:28,240 --> 00:31:30,080
You're still here? The guy already left.

389
00:31:31,880 --> 00:31:34,720
Came together but didn't leave together.
Are they gonna make it?

390
00:31:45,920 --> 00:31:48,880
I told you we should be just friends.

391
00:32:03,640 --> 00:32:05,680
So the meeting's resolution
is unanimous, yes?

392
00:32:05,760 --> 00:32:09,440
Then we can appoint Mr. Rachen
as the new CEO of Be Rich.

393
00:32:12,160 --> 00:32:13,880
Isn't that a bit authoritarian?

394
00:32:17,920 --> 00:32:19,440
We haven't even voted yet.

395
00:32:21,560 --> 00:32:24,760
And Mrs. Mook is in such a hurry
and wouldn't wait for a major shareholder.

396
00:32:24,840 --> 00:32:27,080
Then let's start now, shall we?

397
00:32:27,160 --> 00:32:28,320
Let's do something simple.

398
00:32:29,200 --> 00:32:32,560
Let's voice by a show of hands.
That way, we won't waste time.

399
00:32:33,160 --> 00:32:34,120
That's good.

400
00:32:36,280 --> 00:32:37,360
So we'll have a quick result.

401
00:32:39,840 --> 00:32:43,200
Any executive committee members
who believe that I,

402
00:32:43,800 --> 00:32:45,480
Trai Bowornmongkolphong,

403
00:32:46,240 --> 00:32:48,760
am suitable
to run Be Rich after my father…

404
00:32:51,600 --> 00:32:53,160
please vote now.

405
00:33:00,040 --> 00:33:03,480
Five people, plus…

406
00:33:04,520 --> 00:33:05,560
That makes six.

407
00:33:06,640 --> 00:33:07,840
Still not even half.

408
00:33:21,000 --> 00:33:21,960
Then,

409
00:33:22,880 --> 00:33:25,440
any members who believe
that Mr. Rachen Bowornmongkolphong

410
00:33:25,520 --> 00:33:26,440
is suitable,

411
00:33:27,040 --> 00:33:28,120
please vote now.

412
00:33:36,680 --> 00:33:37,760
Mr. Namchai.

413
00:33:40,280 --> 00:33:42,080
Whether you're here to offer me
something or threaten me,

414
00:33:42,680 --> 00:33:44,200
I can't vote for you, Mr. Trai.

415
00:33:44,800 --> 00:33:46,040
I think the same thing.

416
00:33:46,120 --> 00:33:48,760
Be Rich's next CEO
shouldn't come from lobbying.

417
00:33:48,840 --> 00:33:50,360
Then why are you here to see me?

418
00:33:50,440 --> 00:33:52,040
I'm here to ask something of you.

419
00:33:52,880 --> 00:33:55,520
I want to compete
with Rachen fair and square.

420
00:33:55,600 --> 00:33:57,840
Let the results speak for themselves
and let us prove our capabilities

421
00:33:57,920 --> 00:33:59,640
without factions or favoritism.

422
00:34:00,640 --> 00:34:02,120
I truly want to do this for Be Rich.

423
00:34:02,200 --> 00:34:05,680
And I hope you'll put Be Rich's
best interests first too, Mr. Namchai.

424
00:34:07,360 --> 00:34:08,720
I still can't decide,

425
00:34:10,080 --> 00:34:12,960
because I've never really seen
Trai's abilities.

426
00:34:13,040 --> 00:34:15,440
And I'm sure everyone here hasn't either.

427
00:34:15,520 --> 00:34:18,880
So, how about we let Trai and Rachen

428
00:34:19,520 --> 00:34:21,680
compete on performance, just once?

429
00:34:22,280 --> 00:34:23,920
What about the work I've delivered so far?

430
00:34:24,000 --> 00:34:26,800
Then let that be your head start.
I'm not complaining.

431
00:34:31,080 --> 00:34:32,160
Why?

432
00:34:33,240 --> 00:34:34,240
Scared?

433
00:34:35,680 --> 00:34:36,680
Don't be.

434
00:34:38,720 --> 00:34:40,520
You're still better than me anyway, right?

435
00:34:50,800 --> 00:34:52,080
What's the competition?

436
00:34:52,680 --> 00:34:55,640
Net profit results
for one quarter, the next 90 days.

437
00:34:56,240 --> 00:34:57,160
Too long.

438
00:34:58,520 --> 00:34:59,960
New customer acquisitions
within one month.

439
00:35:00,040 --> 00:35:02,200
Whoever gets more customers
is better suited for the position.

440
00:35:02,280 --> 00:35:04,000
-Deal.
-Deal.

441
00:35:17,640 --> 00:35:19,520
Mr. Rachen already has a big head start.

442
00:35:19,600 --> 00:35:20,640
He already has an app.

443
00:35:20,720 --> 00:35:23,520
He can just launch it
and easily get new customers.

444
00:35:24,280 --> 00:35:26,160
You really shouldn't have competed
with Mr. Rachen on this.

445
00:35:27,960 --> 00:35:28,960
You want to try my way?

446
00:35:36,360 --> 00:35:37,680
Everyone probably thinks

447
00:35:37,760 --> 00:35:40,880
borrowing within the system
is complicated, right?

448
00:35:40,960 --> 00:35:43,600
You have to prepare documents, pay slips,

449
00:35:43,680 --> 00:35:44,880
or collateral.

450
00:35:44,960 --> 00:35:47,560
Just thinking about it
already gives you a headache, right?

451
00:35:47,640 --> 00:35:50,080
So most people
turn to loan sharks instead.

452
00:35:50,160 --> 00:35:52,880
Sign and boom, instant approval.

453
00:35:53,480 --> 00:35:54,680
But everyone, don't forget

454
00:35:54,760 --> 00:35:57,440
the long-term consequences are scary.

455
00:36:01,120 --> 00:36:02,440
Let me give you an example.

456
00:36:03,040 --> 00:36:05,200
Let's say you borrow 20,000.

457
00:36:05,280 --> 00:36:07,720
Outside the system,
the interest rate is 30% per month.

458
00:36:08,360 --> 00:36:10,080
But in the system,

459
00:36:10,160 --> 00:36:13,880
it's 24% per year or 1.13% per month.

460
00:36:14,480 --> 00:36:15,480
In simple terms,

461
00:36:15,560 --> 00:36:17,440
before you borrow,
you have to check the terms carefully.

462
00:36:18,040 --> 00:36:20,120
What's the interest rate?
What are the contract terms?

463
00:36:20,200 --> 00:36:22,360
And you must choose a trustworthy company.

464
00:36:22,440 --> 00:36:24,800
Ms. Darin has quite a lot of followers.

465
00:36:25,400 --> 00:36:28,040
So when she goes live,
people pay attention. And Mr. Trai

466
00:36:28,120 --> 00:36:29,800
is using himself as the hook,

467
00:36:29,880 --> 00:36:31,520
so the viewership keeps increasing.

468
00:36:31,600 --> 00:36:33,200
I'd say Mr. Trai
has caught up pretty fast.

469
00:36:35,680 --> 00:36:38,000
MRS. MOOKMANEE

470
00:36:49,400 --> 00:36:50,800
Yes?

471
00:36:50,880 --> 00:36:52,560
You've seen the viewer numbers, right?

472
00:36:53,760 --> 00:36:54,640
Yes, I have.

473
00:36:54,720 --> 00:36:57,400
You shouldn't have agreed
to play your brother's game.

474
00:36:57,480 --> 00:36:59,360
What if he gets more customers than you?

475
00:37:00,840 --> 00:37:02,120
You don't believe in me?

476
00:37:02,720 --> 00:37:03,800
You're capable,

477
00:37:04,880 --> 00:37:06,520
capable within rules and frameworks.

478
00:37:07,120 --> 00:37:10,520
You've seen it. Your brother
is good at playing outside the game.

479
00:37:11,120 --> 00:37:12,480
You won't be able to keep up.

480
00:37:14,160 --> 00:37:16,080
What if I try playing
outside the game too?

481
00:37:19,240 --> 00:37:20,920
Someone commented and asked

482
00:37:21,000 --> 00:37:23,440
if they wanted to be
Mr. Trai's favorite debtor,

483
00:37:23,520 --> 00:37:24,760
what would they have to do?

484
00:37:24,840 --> 00:37:26,120
IF I WANT TO BE MR. TRAI'S FAVORITE
DEBTOR, WHAT WOULD I HAVE TO DO?

485
00:37:27,160 --> 00:37:30,320
Just sign up for
the "Borrow Smart" program from Be Rich.

486
00:37:30,400 --> 00:37:33,080
This program is under my supervision.
Low interest,

487
00:37:33,160 --> 00:37:34,480
fast approval.

488
00:37:34,560 --> 00:37:38,320
But there's a condition. You must attend
a monthly training on money management.

489
00:37:39,440 --> 00:37:40,280
Hey.

490
00:37:41,360 --> 00:37:43,960
I thought you and Mr. Trai
already cleared things up.

491
00:37:46,040 --> 00:37:48,680
We did. We're friends.

492
00:37:49,600 --> 00:37:50,800
Just friends.

493
00:37:51,480 --> 00:37:53,520
Being friends is the safest option.

494
00:38:05,000 --> 00:38:07,560
MR. RACHEN

495
00:38:16,720 --> 00:38:18,480
Even without a salary,
you can still borrow money with us.

496
00:38:18,560 --> 00:38:20,400
But you must attend the training.

497
00:38:20,480 --> 00:38:22,120
And if you complete it
and follow the rules,

498
00:38:22,200 --> 00:38:23,360
your interest rate will be reduced too.

499
00:38:23,440 --> 00:38:25,640
Really? And what do you train us on?

500
00:38:25,720 --> 00:38:27,600
Money management.

501
00:38:27,680 --> 00:38:28,600
Just like the program name.

502
00:38:28,680 --> 00:38:31,640
"Borrow Smart",
so you can clear your debts faster.

503
00:38:31,720 --> 00:38:34,080
-Then I want to join too, please.
-Sure.

504
00:38:34,160 --> 00:38:35,480
Da.

505
00:38:35,560 --> 00:38:37,160
This way, please.

506
00:38:38,200 --> 00:38:40,440
Mr. Trai is here
like he's campaigning for votes.

507
00:38:41,160 --> 00:38:44,160
But why, why?

508
00:38:45,320 --> 00:38:47,560
Why did he have to pick
our neighborhood first?

509
00:38:48,560 --> 00:38:51,080
Who's he here for?

510
00:38:53,360 --> 00:38:54,720
For customers, obviously.

511
00:38:58,520 --> 00:38:59,720
Hello.

512
00:39:02,840 --> 00:39:06,040
Hey, wait. Go say hi to Mr. Trai first.

513
00:39:18,360 --> 00:39:19,400
Yes.

514
00:39:27,280 --> 00:39:28,880
Oh, hey.

515
00:39:31,320 --> 00:39:32,920
-Yes.
-Excuse me.

516
00:39:33,000 --> 00:39:35,320
If I'm a daily wage worker
with no collateral,

517
00:39:35,400 --> 00:39:36,640
can I borrow from you?

518
00:39:37,640 --> 00:39:38,640
Let's go do our job.

519
00:39:50,160 --> 00:39:51,920
I'll go with Mr. Rachen now.

520
00:39:52,520 --> 00:39:54,520
-Hey, but…
-Don't worry.

521
00:39:56,760 --> 00:39:58,080
Da, please take care of this for me.

522
00:39:59,120 --> 00:40:01,960
BORROW SMART

523
00:40:10,240 --> 00:40:11,400
Pakbung!

524
00:40:15,280 --> 00:40:16,520
Hey, hey.

525
00:40:16,600 --> 00:40:18,120
Pakbung's my person now.

526
00:40:21,080 --> 00:40:24,520
I'm a person, yes,
but I'm not anyone's property, okay?

527
00:40:25,160 --> 00:40:27,320
-We need to talk.
-Hey, hold on.

528
00:40:27,400 --> 00:40:28,840
This time, I paid first.

529
00:40:30,000 --> 00:40:32,120
Come to think of it,
I always pay before you.

530
00:40:33,240 --> 00:40:35,800
Well, Mr. Rachen hired Petch's company

531
00:40:35,880 --> 00:40:37,080
to run the app launch event.

532
00:40:38,200 --> 00:40:39,760
He already paid half as a deposit.

533
00:40:40,400 --> 00:40:43,280
That's my project.
I'm the one who hired you.

534
00:40:43,360 --> 00:40:46,320
Hey, your project got suspended
because Dad died,

535
00:40:46,400 --> 00:40:49,080
and you forgot it. You didn't care,

536
00:40:49,160 --> 00:40:50,800
because you were busy with…

537
00:40:50,880 --> 00:40:52,560
Oh, there. Right on time.

538
00:40:54,040 --> 00:40:55,040
Trai.

539
00:40:56,120 --> 00:40:57,440
Don't start a scene.

540
00:40:59,640 --> 00:41:01,520
We don't know
if someone's secretly filming.

541
00:41:02,920 --> 00:41:05,200
Let's go back and do our job.

542
00:41:08,920 --> 00:41:11,280
Let's go, Mr. Rachen. Let's go do our job.

543
00:41:16,760 --> 00:41:18,400
You already took Dad's leftovers.

544
00:41:19,200 --> 00:41:21,560
So get ready to take mine next, Trai.

545
00:41:23,840 --> 00:41:25,160
How the hell can you say that?!

546
00:41:25,240 --> 00:41:26,160
How can you say that?!

547
00:41:26,240 --> 00:41:27,360
How can you say that?!

548
00:41:27,960 --> 00:41:29,760
Trai, don't! Trai.

549
00:41:30,400 --> 00:41:31,600
Trai.

550
00:41:32,200 --> 00:41:33,280
-Don't.
-I beg you.

551
00:41:33,920 --> 00:41:34,800
Don't fight.

552
00:41:51,400 --> 00:41:52,600
We already kissed, Pakbung.

553
00:42:07,320 --> 00:42:09,520
Mr. Rachen, let's go.

554
00:42:40,680 --> 00:42:41,720
How's the training workshop plan?

555
00:42:42,840 --> 00:42:44,560
This is the draft I put together.

556
00:42:52,800 --> 00:42:54,840
If it's just academic training,

557
00:42:55,480 --> 00:42:56,480
won't it be too boring?

558
00:43:00,080 --> 00:43:01,400
I was thinking the same thing.

559
00:43:04,680 --> 00:43:08,240
What activity can we do that's fun
and teaches them something?

560
00:43:12,120 --> 00:43:13,320
Your brain won't function

561
00:43:14,640 --> 00:43:16,240
if your heart's still hung up.

562
00:43:19,440 --> 00:43:20,800
Did you see Pakbung yet?

563
00:43:23,920 --> 00:43:25,480
You still haven't cleared things up?

564
00:43:27,280 --> 00:43:29,600
I think Rachen is using Pakbung.

565
00:43:30,800 --> 00:43:31,960
But from what I've seen,

566
00:43:32,720 --> 00:43:34,720
Pakbung is really smart.

567
00:43:34,800 --> 00:43:36,280
She shouldn't be easy to fool.

568
00:43:36,360 --> 00:43:38,120
But being fooled
is still better than this.

569
00:43:40,200 --> 00:43:41,640
I don't want her to do this willingly.

570
00:43:43,000 --> 00:43:45,480
How serious are you about Pakbung, Trai?

571
00:43:51,480 --> 00:43:52,480
I like Pakbung.

572
00:43:59,600 --> 00:44:02,760
And… does Pakbung

573
00:44:03,760 --> 00:44:05,320
like you too?

574
00:44:24,560 --> 00:44:25,880
Then…

575
00:44:27,000 --> 00:44:28,080
I'll help you.

576
00:44:34,080 --> 00:44:36,920
Why'd you stop, Petch? What is it?

577
00:44:37,000 --> 00:44:38,920
N-No. Nothing.

578
00:44:39,000 --> 00:44:39,840
-Don't look.
-Then go.

579
00:44:39,920 --> 00:44:41,000
-Don't look.
-Huh?

580
00:44:41,080 --> 00:44:41,960
Don't look.

581
00:44:46,240 --> 00:44:47,680
Again?

582
00:44:48,280 --> 00:44:49,800
Déjà vu, huh?

583
00:44:49,880 --> 00:44:51,440
Don't get upset yet.

584
00:44:53,560 --> 00:44:54,720
What are you doing?

585
00:44:55,520 --> 00:44:56,640
I'll handle it.

586
00:44:57,560 --> 00:44:58,840
Handle what?

587
00:44:59,720 --> 00:45:01,200
Reading their lips.

588
00:45:01,840 --> 00:45:02,960
Huh?

589
00:45:05,200 --> 00:45:06,200
Thank you, Da.

590
00:45:08,000 --> 00:45:10,680
"Thank you so much, Da,

591
00:45:11,720 --> 00:45:14,400
for always being with me."

592
00:45:17,600 --> 00:45:19,240
Hey!

593
00:45:21,720 --> 00:45:24,680
You… You okay?

594
00:45:25,800 --> 00:45:29,480
I'm not okay. I'm hungry!

595
00:45:30,120 --> 00:45:32,120
Then let's go find something to eat, okay?

596
00:45:32,200 --> 00:45:33,720
Let's go.

597
00:45:38,720 --> 00:45:39,840
I booked a table for you.

598
00:45:40,840 --> 00:45:43,400
Are you treating us to a meal?

599
00:45:53,760 --> 00:45:54,920
Outfit and shoes.

600
00:45:56,040 --> 00:45:56,880
Go change.

601
00:45:58,960 --> 00:45:59,960
Oh…

602
00:46:00,520 --> 00:46:03,680
So it's probably for just Pakbung.

603
00:46:06,760 --> 00:46:08,040
-Mr. Rut.
-Yes?

604
00:46:08,600 --> 00:46:09,800
Are you free?

605
00:46:15,640 --> 00:46:16,840
He probably won't go.

606
00:46:38,920 --> 00:46:41,360
So this is how rich people live?

607
00:46:42,320 --> 00:46:43,320
You like it?

608
00:46:48,640 --> 00:46:50,120
I can't answer yet

609
00:46:50,880 --> 00:46:52,280
because I'm not rich yet.

610
00:46:53,600 --> 00:46:55,640
When I get rich on my own,

611
00:46:56,240 --> 00:46:57,320
I'll tell you again, okay?

612
00:46:58,120 --> 00:46:59,320
It probably won't be long.

613
00:47:01,000 --> 00:47:02,040
Why?

614
00:47:09,440 --> 00:47:11,000
This is a rice cracker.

615
00:47:18,640 --> 00:47:20,880
It's not awkward at all. Please continue.

616
00:47:20,960 --> 00:47:22,960
In the center is bluefin tuna,

617
00:47:23,040 --> 00:47:24,200
akami,

618
00:47:24,880 --> 00:47:26,640
chutoro, otoro,

619
00:47:26,720 --> 00:47:28,600
and mentaiko.

620
00:47:28,680 --> 00:47:31,960
On top is beluga caviar.

621
00:47:33,240 --> 00:47:34,440
-Please enjoy.
-Lu-kha…

622
00:47:35,320 --> 00:47:36,400
Lu-kha?

623
00:47:36,480 --> 00:47:37,760
Just eat, Pakbung.

624
00:47:47,080 --> 00:47:48,040
Eat it.

625
00:48:29,560 --> 00:48:31,240
Now this is better.

626
00:48:31,320 --> 00:48:35,320
Way more comfortable!

627
00:48:38,240 --> 00:48:40,040
Were you not comfortable
being with Rachen?

628
00:48:40,120 --> 00:48:41,440
You scared me!

629
00:48:44,760 --> 00:48:46,360
What are you even doing here?

630
00:48:47,200 --> 00:48:48,520
I came to see Kanah.

631
00:48:51,400 --> 00:48:52,400
Then, go ahead.

632
00:48:54,120 --> 00:48:55,440
Are you running away again?

633
00:48:57,560 --> 00:48:59,280
Who's running from who, exactly?

634
00:49:00,840 --> 00:49:03,040
Well, at the beach, you left first.

635
00:49:04,360 --> 00:49:05,840
-I went to buy soy milk.
-I had to rush to work.

636
00:49:10,920 --> 00:49:14,040
I woke up first, so I went out
to buy soy milk for you.

637
00:49:14,920 --> 00:49:16,600
-Soy milk?
-Yes.

638
00:49:17,200 --> 00:49:21,080
And fried dough sticks too.
But when I came back, you were gone.

639
00:49:22,480 --> 00:49:24,960
That day, I woke up,
and you weren't there,

640
00:49:25,040 --> 00:49:26,480
so I thought you left early.

641
00:49:27,080 --> 00:49:28,960
How could I have left early?

642
00:49:29,040 --> 00:49:32,200
You still hadn't paid me for the ride.
And you didn't pay for the room either.

643
00:49:33,320 --> 00:49:34,760
Okay, okay, I'm sorry.

644
00:49:35,960 --> 00:49:38,720
There was a problem at work,
so I had to rush back to deal with it.

645
00:49:38,800 --> 00:49:39,720
I didn't get to call you.

646
00:49:42,120 --> 00:49:45,520
But you didn't tell me
that you took a job from Rachen either.

647
00:49:46,400 --> 00:49:48,600
Rachen contacted Petch directly.

648
00:49:49,160 --> 00:49:50,480
Petch was really happy.

649
00:49:50,560 --> 00:49:51,720
How could I turn it down?

650
00:49:53,440 --> 00:49:54,640
Okay, okay.

651
00:49:55,320 --> 00:49:57,840
I'm sorry I didn't tell you first.

652
00:50:00,960 --> 00:50:04,720
But you already have
your partner, don't you?

653
00:50:07,880 --> 00:50:10,040
"Thank you, Da,

654
00:50:10,120 --> 00:50:12,360
for always being with me."

655
00:50:12,960 --> 00:50:15,440
Hold on. When did I ever say that?

656
00:50:15,520 --> 00:50:18,440
When you were holding Ms. Darin's hand,

657
00:50:19,040 --> 00:50:23,040
looking into each other's eyes
all sweet at the office this afternoon.

658
00:50:26,080 --> 00:50:27,120
Thank you, Da,

659
00:50:28,880 --> 00:50:30,440
but just help with the work is enough.

660
00:50:33,000 --> 00:50:35,520
-Then what Petch read off your lips…
-He read my lips?

661
00:50:40,840 --> 00:50:41,920
Never mind.

662
00:50:43,520 --> 00:50:45,640
Let's just say we're all clear now.

663
00:50:46,240 --> 00:50:48,360
Nothing left hanging, okay?

664
00:50:49,160 --> 00:50:50,680
-There is.
-What?

665
00:50:52,600 --> 00:50:53,720
I'm hungry.

666
00:50:58,680 --> 00:50:59,800
Wow! I want that one!

667
00:50:59,880 --> 00:51:00,840
This one.

668
00:51:00,920 --> 00:51:03,440
-Give me this one.
-Is the heat at the highest setting yet?

669
00:51:04,200 --> 00:51:06,200
I finally get to eat it!

670
00:51:06,280 --> 00:51:07,880
-Okay.
-You're crazy.

671
00:51:09,200 --> 00:51:10,400
Pakbung.

672
00:51:10,480 --> 00:51:12,960
You said you ate omakase,

673
00:51:13,600 --> 00:51:15,720
so why are you slurping like that?

674
00:51:16,480 --> 00:51:17,760
Because I'm not full.

675
00:51:18,880 --> 00:51:22,760
It's like you go for the content,
not to actually feel full.

676
00:51:25,560 --> 00:51:28,520
Like a YouTuber, huh?

677
00:51:28,600 --> 00:51:30,600
Get used to it.

678
00:51:30,680 --> 00:51:34,000
In case Mr. Rachen takes you again.

679
00:51:34,920 --> 00:51:35,880
Yeah.

680
00:51:35,960 --> 00:51:38,920
Petch said Mr. Rachen

681
00:51:39,000 --> 00:51:41,880
bought you a dress too, right?

682
00:51:41,960 --> 00:51:44,880
A super pretty one, right? Right?

683
00:51:47,680 --> 00:51:50,480
Of course it was pretty.
The person wearing it was pretty.

684
00:51:51,040 --> 00:51:52,720
I look good in anything.

685
00:51:54,040 --> 00:51:55,200
Pretty but uncomfortable, huh?

686
00:51:56,160 --> 00:51:59,160
Who said that? It's comfy as hell.

687
00:52:01,040 --> 00:52:04,280
If it's comfy, then why'd you change back
into this baggy home outfit?

688
00:52:04,880 --> 00:52:07,120
Home clothes are for home.

689
00:52:07,720 --> 00:52:10,320
You want me to wear a fancy dress

690
00:52:10,400 --> 00:52:12,480
to sit and eat BBQ?

691
00:52:13,600 --> 00:52:14,640
It'll ruin its value.

692
00:52:14,720 --> 00:52:15,800
Whoa.

693
00:52:16,760 --> 00:52:19,040
Then what's that pile
on the chair by the door?

694
00:52:19,120 --> 00:52:20,320
Fancy dress, isn't it?

695
00:52:20,920 --> 00:52:22,320
Not ruining its value at all?

696
00:52:23,320 --> 00:52:24,920
-Oh. What?
-Well.

697
00:52:25,520 --> 00:52:27,080
Well…

698
00:52:27,160 --> 00:52:28,960
Be honest.

699
00:52:29,040 --> 00:52:32,000
Think carefully.
Are you just not used to that life,

700
00:52:32,080 --> 00:52:34,280
or are you just not into it?

701
00:52:34,360 --> 00:52:35,600
Yeah.

702
00:52:36,320 --> 00:52:37,960
Alright.

703
00:52:38,040 --> 00:52:39,840
Let's make it easy.

704
00:52:39,920 --> 00:52:41,680
We'll play a quickfire Q&A.

705
00:52:41,760 --> 00:52:42,760
-That's good.
-Yeah.

706
00:52:42,840 --> 00:52:44,160
-Yeah. Do it.
-Come on.

707
00:52:44,240 --> 00:52:45,920
-Fine dining or BBQ?
-BBQ.

708
00:52:46,000 --> 00:52:47,360
-Mall or market?
-Market.

709
00:52:47,440 --> 00:52:49,240
-Gambling or working?
-Working.

710
00:52:49,320 --> 00:52:50,800
-Mr. Rachen or Trai?
-Trai.

711
00:52:58,160 --> 00:52:59,640
-Busted!
-Busted!

712
00:53:01,600 --> 00:53:04,080
Wow. Trai?

713
00:53:04,160 --> 00:53:07,200
Honestly, that's pretty cute.

714
00:53:10,080 --> 00:53:11,840
No, that's not it.

715
00:53:12,560 --> 00:53:15,320
Kanah, you cheater!

716
00:53:15,400 --> 00:53:18,640
You saved the answer
I'd slip up on for last.

717
00:53:18,720 --> 00:53:20,160
You totally tricked me.

718
00:53:21,560 --> 00:53:22,920
No one's eating the papaya salad?

719
00:53:23,000 --> 00:53:24,000
I am.

720
00:53:31,520 --> 00:53:35,200
Right now, 245 people have applied
to join Mr. Trai's program.

721
00:53:35,800 --> 00:53:38,600
As for Mr. Rachen's app,

722
00:53:38,680 --> 00:53:39,840
it has 1,400 downloads.

723
00:53:40,440 --> 00:53:43,280
Rachen had Petch's company
organize our event?

724
00:53:43,360 --> 00:53:44,920
Yes, ma'am.

725
00:53:45,000 --> 00:53:48,400
Once we started promoting
the prize giveaways per Mr. Petch's plan,

726
00:53:49,040 --> 00:53:50,720
the app downloads doubled.

727
00:53:52,520 --> 00:53:53,680
That's interesting.

728
00:53:54,880 --> 00:53:56,920
Nothing makes you happier

729
00:53:57,000 --> 00:53:59,280
than doing the work you love.

730
00:54:00,520 --> 00:54:04,160
As for the lawsuit,
whoever wants to sue, go ahead.

731
00:54:04,240 --> 00:54:07,440
Life has to move forward, right?

732
00:54:10,720 --> 00:54:13,000
You're amazing, Petch. That's the spirit.

733
00:54:14,480 --> 00:54:16,360
Don't worry about the lawsuit.

734
00:54:16,440 --> 00:54:18,920
Mr. Trai already found the best lawyer.

735
00:54:19,680 --> 00:54:22,600
Mr. Trai, thank you so much.

736
00:54:23,400 --> 00:54:26,040
No problem, Petch.
But can I ask for one thing?

737
00:54:27,080 --> 00:54:30,520
If you take another job from Rachen,
please tell me first.

738
00:54:31,880 --> 00:54:33,760
-Yes.
-Then next time,

739
00:54:33,840 --> 00:54:35,840
you should hire us before your brother.

740
00:54:36,440 --> 00:54:37,480
No.

741
00:54:39,680 --> 00:54:40,720
Huh?

742
00:54:44,320 --> 00:54:46,400
Be Rich is
a very dangerous place, Pakbung.

743
00:54:47,160 --> 00:54:49,240
Even I almost died.
I can't let you take that risk.

744
00:54:51,560 --> 00:54:52,800
Kanah, Kanah.

745
00:54:57,080 --> 00:54:58,000
Yes?

746
00:54:58,080 --> 00:55:01,520
How far have those two
gotten already? I can't keep up.

747
00:55:03,600 --> 00:55:04,880
Bung.

748
00:55:05,760 --> 00:55:07,160
How far have you and Trai gone?

749
00:55:13,560 --> 00:55:16,840
How far what? Nothing has changed.

750
00:55:16,920 --> 00:55:19,600
-We're friends.
-Friends?

751
00:55:20,840 --> 00:55:21,960
What kind of friends would k--

752
00:55:25,440 --> 00:55:26,880
No. Don't say it.

753
00:55:31,600 --> 00:55:34,920
K… what?

754
00:55:35,480 --> 00:55:38,600
K… Kiss, right?

755
00:55:38,680 --> 00:55:40,360
Huh? You kissed already?

756
00:55:40,440 --> 00:55:41,760
-Huh?!
-Huh?!

757
00:55:43,200 --> 00:55:44,520
Kiss what? Where?

758
00:55:45,280 --> 00:55:46,560
Well, at the beach.

759
00:55:51,560 --> 00:55:52,560
Enough. What?

760
00:55:52,640 --> 00:55:53,800
Don't say it.

761
00:55:54,400 --> 00:55:56,680
No need to cover it up.
Everyone already knows.

762
00:55:59,200 --> 00:56:01,200
Or are you the only one

763
00:56:01,280 --> 00:56:05,920
who doesn't know your own heart?

764
00:56:06,000 --> 00:56:07,760
-Right?
-Or maybe

765
00:56:07,840 --> 00:56:10,800
you do know, but you won't admit it?

766
00:56:10,880 --> 00:56:14,080
Yeah!

767
00:56:14,160 --> 00:56:19,320
You won't admit it,
but you already k-k-kissed?

768
00:56:21,880 --> 00:56:23,880
-K…
-K…

769
00:56:23,960 --> 00:56:27,320
-Kiss.
-Kiss.

770
00:56:27,400 --> 00:56:29,560
Fine! We kissed!

771
00:56:29,640 --> 00:56:31,360
-Huh?
-Oh.

772
00:56:34,320 --> 00:56:37,000
So what? How much do you want?

773
00:56:43,480 --> 00:56:46,960
I've got 200. Kissed. Paid. Done.

774
00:56:47,040 --> 00:56:48,480
Happy now? I'm leaving.

775
00:56:49,080 --> 00:56:50,800
-Hey. What?
-Oh?

776
00:56:51,920 --> 00:56:53,600
-Only 200 for a kiss?
-Is she crazy?

777
00:56:53,680 --> 00:56:54,600
She pays money when she gets shy?

778
00:56:58,000 --> 00:56:59,880
Oh, Pakbung.

779
00:57:02,400 --> 00:57:04,240
He's following her.

780
00:57:06,480 --> 00:57:07,440
Pakbung…

781
00:57:10,280 --> 00:57:12,880
You don't have
to admit it right now. But please,

782
00:57:13,600 --> 00:57:14,560
don't run away.

783
00:57:16,400 --> 00:57:20,120
If you're scared,
I'll make you feel secure.

784
00:57:22,920 --> 00:57:25,480
But I won't throw money at you
like Rachen does.

785
00:57:26,960 --> 00:57:28,440
Then what will you throw at me?

786
00:57:44,520 --> 00:57:45,520
Don't tell me…

787
00:57:46,240 --> 00:57:47,240
Your body?

788
00:57:48,280 --> 00:57:49,320
No.

789
00:57:51,600 --> 00:57:53,040
Then I'll use my heart

790
00:57:54,160 --> 00:57:55,240
to open yours.

791
00:58:20,280 --> 00:58:22,560
Ow! Why did you kick me?

792
00:58:24,920 --> 00:58:27,840
If I didn't kick you,
I'd end up giving it up.

793
00:58:29,160 --> 00:58:30,480
No thanks.

794
00:58:31,080 --> 00:58:32,280
Don't follow me.

795
00:58:37,240 --> 00:58:38,480
Are the boys still intact?

796
00:58:42,680 --> 00:58:44,280
The speaker called
and said he can't make it.

797
00:58:44,360 --> 00:58:45,240
He wants to cancel today's job.

798
00:58:45,320 --> 00:58:47,240
Transfer money to that speaker too.

799
00:58:47,320 --> 00:58:49,120
He went out of his way
to suddenly be "busy" for us.

800
00:58:49,200 --> 00:58:50,560
-Everyone!
-Go, go!

801
00:58:50,640 --> 00:58:51,960
-Please calm down.
-What's this?

802
00:58:52,040 --> 00:58:53,520
-Da.
-Calm down. Is there a fire?

803
00:58:53,600 --> 00:58:55,240
If you getting close to me

804
00:58:55,320 --> 00:58:57,680
means you have
to risk your life like today,

805
00:58:57,760 --> 00:58:58,880
then I--

806
00:59:00,400 --> 00:59:02,160
Trai…

807
00:59:02,240 --> 00:59:04,960
Why does he have to take
my happiness away?!

808
00:59:05,040 --> 00:59:06,800
You don't have to compete

809
00:59:06,880 --> 00:59:08,600
if Mr. Trai is gone from this world.

810
00:59:08,680 --> 00:59:10,240
The world without Trai, huh?

811
00:59:15,280 --> 00:59:17,760
Who do you think you are,
picking a fight with Ms. Mika?

812
00:59:18,760 --> 00:59:20,720
She deserved her dad to slap her for me.

813
00:59:20,800 --> 00:59:22,680
And it won't end with just a slap.

814
00:59:22,760 --> 00:59:24,600
Money's the most
important thing in life, right?

815
00:59:24,680 --> 00:59:26,640
So important you can pay a father

816
00:59:26,720 --> 00:59:28,040
to slap his own daughter.

817
00:59:28,120 --> 00:59:29,320
Pakbung.

818
00:59:30,320 --> 00:59:31,360
Ms. Mika, watch out!
